{"title": "Possible dangerous serialization configuration", "summary": " JSON is the safest serialization strategy for untrusted data, such as cookie data, to avoid malicious code injection. By default, Rails uses JSON to serialize cookie values. ", "description": "\nJSON is the safest serialization strategy for untrusted data, such as cookie data, to avoid malicious code injection. By default, Rails uses JSON to serialize cookie values.\n", "recommendations": "\n\u274c Avoid overriding the default cookie serializer\n\n```ruby\nRails.application.config.action_dispatch.cookies_serializer = :marshal\n```\n\n\u274c Use the hybrid (Marshal and JSON) serializer option as a temporary solution only, for example when migrating from Marshal to JSON.\n\n```ruby\nRails.application.config.action_dispatch.cookies_serializer = :hybrid\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-502"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/ruby_rails_unsafe_cookie_serialization_strategy", "https://github.com/OWASP/railsgoat/wiki/Extras:-Remote-Code-Execution"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}